# Cursor AI Rules for asc-wordpress-tools

This project follows the coding style guidelines defined in `STYLE_GUIDE.md`. Please review and follow those guidelines when writing or modifying code.

## Key Style Preferences

- Use null coalescing operator (`??`) for simple defaults
- Use switch statements where appropriate
- Use explicit if statements for conditional logic - avoid ternary operators and conditional assignment
- Use tabs for indentation (no spaces for column alignment)
- Separate logic from HTML presentation - do all data preparation before HTML blocks
- Pre-compute variables before HTML blocks
- Use descriptive variable names

## Important Patterns

### Avoid Conditional Assignment
Instead of: `$is_manual = 'none' === $selected_model;`
Use:
```php
$is_manual = false;
if ( 'none' === $selected_model ) {
	$is_manual = true;
}
```

### Avoid Ternary Operators
Instead of: `$class = $is_active ? 'active' : 'inactive';`
Use:
```php
$class = 'inactive';
if ( $is_active ) {
	$class = 'active';
}
```

### Separate Logic from HTML
Do all data preparation and logic before HTML blocks. Use plain variables in HTML, not complex expressions.

For complete guidelines, see `STYLE_GUIDE.md`.
